  "original_title": "Sri Lanka schedules 3-hour power cuts from Aug 16 to 19",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka schedules 3-hour power cuts from Aug 16 to 19",
      "author": "Dulya de Silva",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has imposed power cuts up to three hours from Tuesday August 16 to Friday August 19\u00a0 after a generator at the Norochcholai coal power plant had a sudden breakdown, the Public Utilities Commission (PUCSL) has said.",
        "All groups (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, P, Q, R, S, T, U, V and W) will have lose power for one hour and 40 minutes during daytime another one hour and 20minutes at night.",
        "Group CC will have a 2 hour and 30 minute power cut from 6.00am to 8.30am.",
        "Board of Investment (BOI) industrial groups (M, N, O, Y and Z) will have 3 hour cuts from 5.30am to 8.30am.",
        "Currently only Unit 3 of the Norochcholai power plant is in operation. Unit 2 is undergoing scheduled maintenance, and repairs on the broken down Unit 1 will take up to a fortnight.",
        "The sudden breakdown meant that power cut durations which were decreased from 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes due to availability of hydroelectricity, had to be increased.\u00a0 (Colombo/Aug15/2022)"
      ],
